{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b2331b76-971f-4517-ba45-cf98f497d0c3","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n- Install the .NET 11 SDK locally (`dotnet --version` to verify).\n- Update NuGet packages (`dotnet outdated` or manually bump `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` / `Microsoft.Extensions.*` references to 11.x).\n- Run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to catch any breaking changes.\n- Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) for breaking changes relevant to your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"181445ba-5cb0-45f4-88d5-8ba31d28081c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the files clearly.","outputTokens":335,"requestId":"E01D:9D55F:C46094:E4F998:69F406F1"},"id":"d8f87d9b-5d7a-4b84-b1ac-02f285776086","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:50:48.739Z","parentId":"67225e53-9805-4bbd-a677-601b0efedfbd"}
